  levelNumber: 7
  levelName: Quirigua
  location: Izabal, Guatemala
  levelDescription: "Quirigu\xE1 reached its height between 700\u2013850 CE, becoming
    a regional power famed for its colossal monuments. Its sculptors carved the tallest
    known Maya stelae\u2014towering stone pillars covered in detailed glyphs and
    portraits of King K\u2019ak\u2019 Tiliw Chan Yopaat and his predecessors. The
    city\u2019s history is marked by a dramatic political triumph when it broke free
    from the dominance of Cop\xE1n, an event celebrated in its inscriptions. Quirigu\xE1\u2019s
    monuments preserve some of the clearest dynastic records, making it essential
    to understanding Classic Maya politics, alliances, and rivalries.\n\nHere, stone
    giants preserved a kingdom\u2019s defiant rise against its powerful neighbor."
  requiredStackHeight: 35
